Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.90,0:01:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Miss Emma, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.40,0:01:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.11,0:01:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was told to deliver this letter\Nto you by the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.86,0:02:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must marry someone from the same country.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.73,0:02:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,England is one nation, but there\Nare two countries within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.57,0:02:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the aristocracy\Nand the commoners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.64,0:02:30.58,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 7\NCrystal Palace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.40,0:02:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that face? If I was\Nthat upset, I'd do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.91,0:03:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.19,0:03:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.26,0:03:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for inviting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.69,0:03:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father sends his regards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.20,0:03:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all rather embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.34,0:03:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all, it's very lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It captures your characteristics well.\NThe artist has a fine touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.51,0:03:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I really look like that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father told me that\NI should invite you for a drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.53,0:03:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that displease you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.86,0:03:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. I'd be delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.93,0:03:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.43,0:03:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor, your portrait is delightful!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.87,0:04:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so elegant!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.50,0:04:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the artist didn't quite capture your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.77,0:04:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to commission a\Ndifferent painter for my portrait.\NPardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.41,0:04:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to commission a\Ndifferent painter for my portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alice, don't be rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! All I meant was that\Nyou're prettier than your portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Miss Eleanor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.26,0:04:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.30,0:04:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Be clearer in your actions. You're\Ngiving her the wrong impression."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you're thinking, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm aware of the situation. I'm not just\Ngoing along with my father's wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.54,0:04:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't said a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.73,0:05:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you have\Nsomething you want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.56,0:05:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.77,0:05:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... may I take a half-day\Nholiday next week, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next week, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.45,0:05:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I know that half a day would\Ninconvenience you... Not to mention...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.49,0:05:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.19,0:05:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. Take the whole day off, if you need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have somewhere you want to go, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.50,0:05:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been such a help to me\Nrecently. You deserve a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.90,0:05:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.94,0:05:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll find a dark red muslin dress\Non the second shelf of the cupboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.51,0:05:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wear that when you go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:06:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was mine when I was younger, so the\Nstyle's old, but I think the size should be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.29,0:06:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should wear nice clothes\Nwhen you meet a young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially a young man that you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.07,0:06:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:06:58.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Crystal Palace?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.38,0:07:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In 1 851, the first Great Exhibition\Nwas held here in London, in Hyde Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.52,0:07:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This modern beauty, made from glass and iron,\Nwas built as pavilion for the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.36,0:07:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A year after the Great Exhibition,\Nit was rebuilt here in Sydenham.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.33,0:07:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Works of art from all around the world,\Neven all sorts of tropical animals and plants...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.17,0:07:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have been gathered together here,\Nto create a paradise on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.54,0:07:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I studied overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the symbol of the Crystal Palace.\NIt's often used as a meeting place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.85,0:07:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 27 feet tall, and was made from\N8,960 pounds of crystal glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.06,0:07:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time of the opening ceremony...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.93,0:07:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.00,0:07:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.00,0:07:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Byzantine Corner is that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:07:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and over here is Romanesque.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.31,0:08:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which way shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.08,0:08:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't really know... Either way is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.68,0:08:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, let's start with the closest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.32,0:08:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This area represents Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.26,0:08:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it real?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.96,0:08:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would appear so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.50,0:08:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a model of the temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.80,0:08:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's this pillar?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.33,0:08:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a part of the entrance.\NIt's so thin when you look at it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.67,0:08:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's more over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.54,0:08:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Egyptian Corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.35,0:08:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how they moved\Nsuch large statues here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.02,0:08:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These sphinxes are for guarding tombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.35,0:08:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all right to bring a tomb's guardian here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.02,0:08:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.63,0:08:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.10,0:09:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.44,0:09:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange, isn't it? That they would spend\Na fortune making such childish things...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The building of the Crystal Palace was\Nopposed by both Parliament and the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.88,0:09:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The plan was nearly quashed several times,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the perseverance and strong will\Nof Prince Albert allowed it to be built.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I look at this shining monument,\Nit gives me the courage to overcome anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must sound very naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.04,0:09:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.61,0:09:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you cold? Let's have\Nsomething hot to drink inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.18,0:09:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.75,0:09:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Café... café...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.72,0:09:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.19,0:09:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.07,0:10:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.86,0:11:09.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.90,0:11:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank heavens. I thought I'd lost you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.00,0:11:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why did you come to this spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you said that the fountain\Nwas used as a meeting place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that you might come back here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too! I had a feeling that you'd be here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we've traveled around the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.90,0:11:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A stroll around the world, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.80,0:11:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.31,0:11:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still more to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:11:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a library, and a moving picture gallery.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.28,0:11:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On Saturdays, there are\Nperformances in the concert hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The northern water tower\Nhas an observation platform...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me dizzy just hearing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.29,0:12:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In summer, they hold fireworks displays.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.29,0:12:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.86,0:12:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we come see it sometime?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.59,0:12:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing! There are fireworks\Nthat look like the Niagara Falls...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.34,0:12:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The exhibition will be closing in 1 5 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The exhibition is closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please make your way to the exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.85,0:12:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are closing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.76,0:12:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And finally they found me, looking\Nat the models, completely nonchalant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, you weren't really lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.63,0:12:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't consider myself lost, either.\NI couldn't understand why he was so angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.74,0:12:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then, I realized that my\Nmother was nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:12:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So my father dragged me and my sister around\Nby the hand, searching for our lost mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.81,0:13:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It's like I have three children,"\Nhe kept complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.02,0:13:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It all seems so long ago now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rather quiet, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.43,0:13:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it that late already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.24,0:13:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun is setting... Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.81,0:13:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.69,0:13:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.56,0:13:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't open?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.46,0:13:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No good. This one's closed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.50,0:14:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Is anyone there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.28,0:14:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Please, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.96,0:14:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. It's turned out to be a terrible day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.87,0:14:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Being here like this gives me such a\Nstrange feeling. I've never been so happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.98,0:14:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but, I'm also afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.85,0:14:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This happiness, it can't last.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.69,0:14:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the feeling I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.13,0:15:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you... feel that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.33,0:15:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because so much has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.30,0:15:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I shouldn't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.67,0:15:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.11,0:15:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the first time I've ever heard\Nyou talk about yourself in this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.94,0:15:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.38,0:15:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where Master William is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.14,0:15:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones is searching for him.\NI thought you might know where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your name is Stevens, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.46,0:16:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Master William's?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.93,0:16:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but please tell Mr. Jones\Nthat his son has already retired to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.60,0:16:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just pretend that you mistook me for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.87,0:16:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.61,0:16:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come now, don't say such boorish things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.38,0:17:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The full moon is so bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.45,0:17:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.22,0:17:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The insects are buzzing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.39,0:17:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the birds are asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.47,0:17:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you sleepy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.24,0:17:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I normally go to bed much later than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.57,0:17:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.01,0:17:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.55,0:17:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.48,0:17:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.86,0:17:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.02,0:17:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.76,0:17:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.21,0:18:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.64,0:18:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I saw so many things that I'd never\Nseen before, I think my eyes must be in shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.94,0:19:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What are you two doing here...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.55,0:19:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... The door's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.16,0:19:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fine morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to have fallen asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.03,0:19:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.67,0:20:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stevens, please close the curtains...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only just gotten to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.41,0:20:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not sleep last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.08,0:20:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.65,0:20:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's William?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.75,0:20:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is sleeping, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.45,0:20:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping? At this time of day?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.92,0:20:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me not to wake him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.92,0:20:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, what on Earth is that boy thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.93,0:20:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And after you went to all this\Ntrouble to come and see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. He must very be tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.21,0:20:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is, Eleanor.\NWe'll ask him out another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.01,0:20:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... the weather has finally turned nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.31,0:20:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't something to be fussing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.52,0:21:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd like, Miss Campbell...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.59,0:21:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William doesn't have a partner for the next ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.23,0:21:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you be gracious enough to accept?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.94,0:21:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William would be happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.77,0:21:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.61,0:21:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to hear that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.95,0:21:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will inform William as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.66,0:21:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.19,0:21:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I slept soundly last night.\NWhat time did you return?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.86,0:21:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.10,0:21:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, what a wonderful smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nearly ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.31,0:24:09.97,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode:\NThe Pocket Watch
